WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

2
00:01:03.897 --> 00:01:06.483
It's not easy
to move past certain things.

3
00:01:08.402 --> 00:01:10.696
I don't know how anyone ever could.

4
00:01:12.823 --> 00:01:13.991
Especially this.

5
00:01:23.458 --> 00:01:26.712
Seventy-five percent
of the world. maybe more.

6
00:01:26.795 --> 00:01:28.213
We still don't know.

7
00:01:29.756 --> 00:01:30.757
Gone.

8
00:01:38.724 --> 00:01:40.684
Five years since impact.

9
00:01:40.767 --> 00:01:42.603
but Clarke wasn't done with us yet.

10
00:01:43.312 --> 00:01:45.522
Fragments stuck in our orbit.

11
00:01:46.273 --> 00:01:48.317
pelting us without warning.

12
00:01:49.443 --> 00:01:51.111
We tried rebuilding.

13
00:01:51.194 --> 00:01:52.738
but the world wasn't ready.

14
00:01:54.197 --> 00:01:56.617
Forcing us back inside.

15
00:01:58.994 --> 00:02:01.204
Radiation hit differently everywhere.

16
00:02:02.247 --> 00:02:04.166
Most places burned out.

17
00:02:04.249 --> 00:02:08.545
Others. for reasons we don't
understand. stayed green.

18
00:02:10.714 --> 00:02:14.468
Life. finding a way
through the contamination.

19
00:02:42.913 --> 00:02:44.456
Our bunker's holding on.

20
00:02:47.292 --> 00:02:48.710
We're doing the best we can.

21
00:02:51.463 --> 00:02:53.632
It's not easy living underground.

22
00:02:56.301 --> 00:02:58.095
But we find joy when we can.

23
00:03:00.639 --> 00:03:01.640
Together.

24
00:03:31.420 --> 00:03:33.422
Microphone check.
One. two. One. two.

25
00:03:36.174 --> 00:03:37.592
Loud and clear. John.

26
00:03:39.469 --> 00:03:42.013
You know what I woke up
thinking about today?

27
00:03:43.932 --> 00:03:45.100
Let's hear it.

28
00:03:46.601 --> 00:03:48.103
Biscuits and gravy.

29
00:03:48.729 --> 00:03:50.439
That'd be nice.

30
00:03:50.981 --> 00:03:53.483
I'd trade my left arm
for a decent cup of coffee.

31
00:03:55.152 --> 00:03:56.862
Peckman's Diner made the best.

32
00:03:56.945 --> 00:03:59.030
Across the street from Piedmont Park.

33
00:03:59.114 --> 00:04:01.825
Walk over for one
of those summer concerts.

34
00:04:01.908 --> 00:04:03.577
Blue sky. grass. people.

35
00:04:04.453 --> 00:04:05.746
Beer.

36
00:04:05.829 --> 00:04:07.497
Sounds like paradise.

37
00:04:07.581 --> 00:04:08.582
Oh. it was.

38
00:04:11.334 --> 00:04:14.463
Jesus. Another fissure's opened up.

39
00:04:14.546 --> 00:04:15.547
More lava?

40
00:04:16.465 --> 00:04:18.008
Yeah. and they're getting bigger.

41
00:04:43.617 --> 00:04:46.244
Okay. looks like we've got
a few lifeboats.

42
00:04:50.457 --> 00:04:51.792
And another ghost ship.

43
00:04:52.667 --> 00:04:53.668
A destroyer.

44
00:04:54.294 --> 00:04:56.838
Nice. Feelin' lucky today?

45
00:04:56.922 --> 00:04:58.965
Always. I'm starting
with the lifeboats.

46
00:04:59.049 --> 00:05:00.091
see what's there.

47
00:05:00.175 --> 00:05:01.384
Good luck out there.

48
00:05:20.028 --> 00:05:21.363
Heading to the destroyer.

49
00:05:25.826 --> 00:05:28.119
We're seeing
a pressure storm building off the coast.

50
00:05:28.203 --> 00:05:30.372
but it looks like
you've got a little time.

51
00:05:30.455 --> 00:05:31.957
I won't hang around.

52
00:05:51.685 --> 00:05:53.019
Jackpot.

53
00:06:01.903 --> 00:06:03.113
Entering the bridge.

54
00:06:08.451 --> 00:06:09.744
Oh. I've found something else.

55
00:06:11.162 --> 00:06:12.372
What is it. John?

56
00:06:14.332 --> 00:06:15.709
The crew.

57
00:06:17.502 --> 00:06:18.628
Shit.

58
00:06:47.449 --> 00:06:48.658
Oh. how beautiful.

59
00:06:51.411 --> 00:06:53.204
John...

60
00:06:54.205 --> 00:06:58.209
John. can you hear me?
John. can you hear me?

61
00:06:58.293 --> 00:06:59.878
That storm just took a turn right for you.

62
00:06:59.961 --> 00:07:02.422
You'd better get outta there
now and get back here!

63
00:07:02.505 --> 00:07:03.506
On my way.

64
00:07:04.424 --> 00:07:07.135
Exiting ship now. How much time do I have?

65
00:07:07.218 --> 00:07:08.762
None.
It's right on top of you.

66
00:07:21.024 --> 00:07:22.525
Come on.

67
00:07:23.610 --> 00:07:25.904
I'm staying ahead of it. but it's gaining.

68
00:07:31.993 --> 00:07:34.454
Shit. base... This one's coming in fast!

69
00:07:37.499 --> 00:07:39.334
John! John. where are you?

70
00:07:40.377 --> 00:07:42.253
I'm moving as fast as I can!

71
00:07:47.342 --> 00:07:48.551
Open the east tunnel!

72
00:07:50.553 --> 00:07:52.347
Open the door!

73
00:07:53.348 --> 00:07:55.016
Open the door! Get it open!

74
00:08:00.146 --> 00:08:03.149
The storm is too close!
We have to close the blast doors. John!

75
00:08:03.233 --> 00:08:04.317
I can make it!

76
00:08:11.533 --> 00:08:13.243
Close. close. close!

77
00:08:13.326 --> 00:08:15.620
-Go. go. go. go. go!
-John. are you in?

78
00:08:48.445 --> 00:08:50.155
Bucharest. Romania.

79
00:08:50.238 --> 00:08:52.866
The city has been destroyed
by the earthquakes.

80
00:08:52.949 --> 00:08:54.075
We're trapped under...

81
00:08:54.617 --> 00:08:56.119
Mumbai. India.

82
00:08:56.202 --> 00:08:57.996
Salt water is still rising fast.

83
00:08:58.079 --> 00:09:00.290
FEMA planned for two years.

84
00:09:00.373 --> 00:09:02.333
We've stretched our resources to five.

85
00:09:02.417 --> 00:09:04.627
So we're basically
running on fumes?

86
00:09:04.711 --> 00:09:07.172
Yes. We are getting too close.

87
00:09:07.922 --> 00:09:11.593
Hopefully in a year
we're outside planting.

88
00:09:13.344 --> 00:09:16.181
Well. we have
measured a 4% reduction

89
00:09:16.264 --> 00:09:19.225
in coulomb per kilogram
in the last three months.

90
00:09:19.309 --> 00:09:22.187
We still can't predict when it'll be
safe levels again. but...

91
00:09:22.270 --> 00:09:24.272
-But it's improving. yeah?
-Yes.

92
00:09:24.355 --> 00:09:25.815
Though that's mostly off the coast.

93
00:09:25.899 --> 00:09:28.943
Yeah. Hopefully the winds will eventually
clear out the radiation.

94
00:09:29.027 --> 00:09:31.112
No. that's not exactly how it works.

95
00:09:31.196 --> 00:09:33.740
Continuous radiation exposure.

96
00:09:33.823 --> 00:09:37.577
even at those low levels
still leads to fatality.

97
00:09:37.660 --> 00:09:39.788
We should discuss our contingency plans.

98
00:09:39.871 --> 00:09:41.498
Okay. yeah. Um...

99
00:09:42.165 --> 00:09:45.210
Canada. and much of the US. gone.

100
00:09:45.752 --> 00:09:47.170
Iceland. gone.

101
00:09:47.712 --> 00:09:48.713
Western Europe?

102
00:09:49.839 --> 00:09:51.633
There are reports
of fewer storms there. right?

103
00:09:51.716 --> 00:09:53.676
-Yes.
-But is the air safe?

104
00:09:55.178 --> 00:09:56.179
Safer than here.

105
00:09:56.262 --> 00:09:59.724
Didn't we just say that
dying slowly is still dying?

106
00:09:59.808 --> 00:10:01.976
I mean. am I right. Dr. Amina?

107
00:10:02.644 --> 00:10:05.105
-Isn't it the same over there?
-Yes.

108
00:10:08.233 --> 00:10:10.777
Dr. Amina. what's the latest
on the crater?

109
00:10:13.863 --> 00:10:17.408
Well. my colleagues at other stations
have theorized the same thing.

110
00:10:18.243 --> 00:10:20.036
And I've run my own calculations.

111
00:10:20.120 --> 00:10:21.204
We can't fully explain it.

112
00:10:21.287 --> 00:10:24.165
but it seems the size
and shape of the crater walls

113
00:10:24.249 --> 00:10:26.793
prevent the radioactive storms
from forming.

114
00:10:26.876 --> 00:10:30.088
This combined with its depth
are what's making it such a safe zone.

115
00:10:30.171 --> 00:10:33.091
We believe it's what's keeping
the polluted air from getting in.

116
00:10:33.174 --> 00:10:35.844
But. Dr. Amina.
even if it was real.

117
00:10:35.927 --> 00:10:37.178
it's in Southern France.

118
00:10:38.555 --> 00:10:40.140
How exactly are we gonna get there?

119
00:10:40.223 --> 00:10:42.016
There have been reports of fighting.

120
00:10:42.100 --> 00:10:44.602
insurgency. civil war.

121
00:10:44.686 --> 00:10:45.687
Europe is in chaos.

122
00:10:47.689 --> 00:10:50.275
Please. let's... let's stick to reality.

123
00:10:55.572 --> 00:10:57.824
Attention residents.
this is your daily reminder

124
00:10:57.907 --> 00:10:59.742
to report any malfunctioning
air filtration...

125
00:10:59.826 --> 00:11:01.494
Please ration carefully and only...

126
00:11:01.578 --> 00:11:04.205
There's people here
who say it's the new normal.

127
00:11:05.290 --> 00:11:06.875
Well. we're going on...

128
00:11:08.001 --> 00:11:09.586
-five years now?
-Mm-hmm.

129
00:11:10.211 --> 00:11:11.421
So it isn't all that new.

130
00:11:12.547 --> 00:11:14.549
And it definitely ain't normal.

131
00:11:14.632 --> 00:11:18.386
You know. it's no accident there were
twice as many therapists selected

132
00:11:18.469 --> 00:11:20.096
as there were surgeons.

133
00:11:20.180 --> 00:11:23.600
People are dealing with an
incredible amount of trauma.

134
00:11:23.683 --> 00:11:25.602
Why does everybody
pretend like they're not. huh?

135
00:11:25.685 --> 00:11:26.895
-Do you?
-Pretend?

136
00:11:26.978 --> 00:11:28.021
Mm-hmm.

137
00:11:29.898 --> 00:11:30.940
Sometimes.

138
00:11:32.150 --> 00:11:33.318
Maybe you should stop.

139
00:11:34.194 --> 00:11:35.778
Well. maybe you can recommend
a good therapist

140
00:11:35.862 --> 00:11:37.030
that can help me with that.

141
00:11:37.947 --> 00:11:38.948
Mine's pretty good.

142
00:11:44.913 --> 00:11:46.414
So. uh...

143
00:11:48.291 --> 00:11:50.835
Allison. Nathan. how are they?

144
00:11:52.253 --> 00:11:54.422
They're getting by. I think. I hope.

145
00:11:56.758 --> 00:11:59.302
Openness is important. Uh...

146
00:12:00.970 --> 00:12:03.014
Well. they're pretty open with me.

147
00:12:04.390 --> 00:12:05.725
I meant the other way around.

148
00:12:21.032 --> 00:12:22.700
Seems like there's been
more of those lately.

149
00:12:24.369 --> 00:12:26.621
The tectonic plates are shifting again.

150
00:12:27.288 --> 00:12:29.916
It's triggering a lot
of activity in this region.

151
00:12:29.999 --> 00:12:31.376
This bunker survived Clarke.

152
00:12:31.960 --> 00:12:33.544
It'll survive tremors.

153
00:12:33.628 --> 00:12:35.505
There's one more thing we should discuss.

154
00:12:36.047 --> 00:12:38.800
The distress signal
we received from outside.

155
00:12:38.883 --> 00:12:41.386
We cannot afford to feed 50 more mouths.

156
00:12:41.469 --> 00:12:43.137
We can't afford five.

157
00:12:43.221 --> 00:12:46.182
I know. but these people are living
in caves and mine shafts.

158
00:12:46.266 --> 00:12:48.393
Yes. and we don't know
if they're bringing disease

159
00:12:48.476 --> 00:12:50.603
or how much radiation they've absorbed.

160
00:12:51.187 --> 00:12:53.189
Okay. We just let them die.

161
00:12:55.733 --> 00:12:58.987
We tell them we are not
currently in a position

162
00:12:59.070 --> 00:13:00.154
to be of assistance.

163
00:13:01.990 --> 00:13:03.241
-Yeah?
-No.

164
00:13:03.324 --> 00:13:05.159
We put it to a vote like everything else.

165
00:13:05.994 --> 00:13:07.787
Motion to send out a rescue party?

166
00:13:09.414 --> 00:13:10.415
I second.

167
00:13:21.175 --> 00:13:22.176
General...

168
00:13:22.927 --> 00:13:24.304
The vote stands.

169
00:13:24.387 --> 00:13:27.056
We'll send out the Snowcat tomorrow.

170
00:13:28.766 --> 00:13:31.519
And as we look at the northern sky.

171
00:13:31.602 --> 00:13:33.771
which constellation is this?

172
00:13:34.397 --> 00:13:36.733
-Gemini?
-No. No. not Gemini.

173
00:13:37.400 --> 00:13:38.443
Nathan?

174
00:13:40.194 --> 00:13:42.363
Oh. um. it's Cassiopeia.

175
00:13:42.447 --> 00:13:43.865
You can tell by its W-shape.

176
00:13:45.074 --> 00:13:47.410
Why do we have to
learn so much about the stars?

177
00:13:47.493 --> 00:13:48.828
Well. maybe we should have paid

178
00:13:48.911 --> 00:13:50.580
a little more attention
to them in the past.

179
00:13:50.663 --> 00:13:52.999
Clarke wasn't a star. it was a comet.

180
00:13:53.082 --> 00:13:55.543
-Still is.
-But it already hit the ground.

181
00:13:56.336 --> 00:13:57.670
The biggest part of it did.

182
00:13:57.754 --> 00:14:00.506
but the smaller bits that didn't.

183
00:14:00.590 --> 00:14:03.426
they got caught
in our gravitational field.

184
00:14:03.509 --> 00:14:06.971
Created what is known as a ghost ring.

185
00:14:15.605 --> 00:14:19.400
You catch my breath
On the morning light

186
00:14:20.109 --> 00:14:23.780
A thousand times
And it still surprises me

187
00:14:23.863 --> 00:14:29.619
I fall asleep where
I like to think our dreams

188
00:14:30.328 --> 00:14:31.496
Collide...

189
00:14:33.373 --> 00:14:35.375
Lars. what is this shit?

190
00:14:35.458 --> 00:14:37.460
What? It's classical rock and roll.

191
00:14:38.044 --> 00:14:41.506
If you mean classic rock.
then this ain't it.

192
00:14:42.632 --> 00:14:45.343
Gimme the Stones. the Altman Brothers...

193
00:14:46.094 --> 00:14:49.180
Michael McDonald.
now that's classical rock.

194
00:14:50.515 --> 00:14:52.600
Billy Ocean. Also pretty cool.

195
00:14:56.062 --> 00:14:58.398
Just turn the valve on already.

196
00:15:07.740 --> 00:15:09.951
Come on. baby. Here we go!

197
00:15:16.541 --> 00:15:18.751
Whoo! Back in business!

198
00:15:18.835 --> 00:15:21.003
Nice!

199
00:15:21.796 --> 00:15:23.548
We can drink some water again.

200
00:15:25.925 --> 00:15:26.926
Mom...

201
00:15:28.261 --> 00:15:30.680
-Mom. I can explain.
-Nathan. I don't want to hear it!

202
00:15:30.763 --> 00:15:32.890
You hear how your dad's
coughing at night. right?

203
00:15:32.974 --> 00:15:34.267
Yeah.

204
00:15:34.350 --> 00:15:35.518
Get in.

205
00:15:38.563 --> 00:15:40.773
Oh. I hate this place.

206
00:15:44.152 --> 00:15:45.903
Come here. I know.

207
00:15:49.532 --> 00:15:50.533
It's okay.

208
00:15:56.998 --> 00:15:58.541
-Do you know it?
-Yes. of course!

209
00:15:58.624 --> 00:15:59.625
Impossible.

210
00:16:00.293 --> 00:16:01.919
Hey. what did I miss?

211
00:16:02.003 --> 00:16:03.796
He has never heard this song.

212
00:16:03.880 --> 00:16:05.590
You've never heard this song before?

213
00:16:05.673 --> 00:16:07.675
- I like it though. huh?
-Yeah? Then come dance.

214
00:16:07.758 --> 00:16:10.595
Oh. okay. Let's... I'm gonna dance
to the song I've never heard.

215
00:16:10.678 --> 00:16:11.804
Good.

216
00:16:12.722 --> 00:16:15.266
Oh. I know it's a little late. but...

217
00:16:15.349 --> 00:16:16.893
Da-da-da-dah.

218
00:16:18.060 --> 00:16:20.062
Happy belated Valentine's Day.

219
00:16:20.146 --> 00:16:22.690
Where'd you find it?

220
00:16:22.773 --> 00:16:25.067
In that destroyer.
Amongst some other stuff.

221
00:16:26.068 --> 00:16:27.528
I can finally fix my radio.

222
00:16:27.612 --> 00:16:29.906
What about the pressure pump
for desalination?

223
00:16:29.989 --> 00:16:32.658
General Sharpe was saying
that the water levels are getting low.

224
00:16:35.578 --> 00:16:36.579
I'm sorry.

225
00:16:37.997 --> 00:16:39.540
I love it. Thank you.

226
00:16:40.750 --> 00:16:42.752
-Whoo!
-Thank you.

227
00:16:43.336 --> 00:16:45.296
What about you. young man?
How was your day?

228
00:16:47.298 --> 00:16:48.341
Fine.

229
00:16:48.883 --> 00:16:51.385
Is there anything else
you wanna say to your father. Nathan?

230
00:16:53.679 --> 00:16:55.598
Security found him outside.

231
00:16:56.182 --> 00:16:58.059
Outside. outside?

232
00:16:58.142 --> 00:16:59.143
Yep.

233
00:16:59.227 --> 00:17:01.145
Are you kidding me?

234
00:17:01.229 --> 00:17:02.730
How long were you out there for?

235
00:17:02.813 --> 00:17:04.023
Only a few minutes.

236
00:17:04.106 --> 00:17:05.650
-Did you wear a mask?
-Yeah.

237
00:17:05.733 --> 00:17:06.984
And there wasn't a storm.

238
00:17:07.068 --> 00:17:09.820
It's too dangerous for you
to be going outside!

239
00:17:09.904 --> 00:17:11.447
-What are you thinking?
- I know.

240
00:17:11.531 --> 00:17:13.366
You told me. the radiation. the ash.

241
00:17:13.449 --> 00:17:14.575
I understand.

242
00:17:16.160 --> 00:17:19.622
Look. son. I know how much
it sucks being down here.

243
00:17:19.705 --> 00:17:21.249
- I get it.
-Try being 15.

244
00:17:21.332 --> 00:17:23.209
Yeah. well. you're not listening to me!

245
00:17:25.670 --> 00:17:27.380
-Look. wait--
-Can I be excused?

246
00:17:35.137 --> 00:17:37.306
He's just trying to figure
things out. I guess.

247
00:17:37.390 --> 00:17:38.641
-No. no...
-He's also sensitive.

248
00:17:38.724 --> 00:17:40.685
No. he's being an idiot.

249
00:17:40.768 --> 00:17:41.769
Like you.

250
00:17:44.146 --> 00:17:45.147
Going outside?

251
00:17:46.399 --> 00:17:47.817
Oh...

252
00:17:47.900 --> 00:17:49.610
Yeah.

253
00:17:50.403 --> 00:17:51.612
Takes after his father.

254
00:17:58.619 --> 00:18:00.121
Everyone I know...

255
00:18:01.622 --> 00:18:03.791
-Come on.
-No. no. Allison. no.

256
00:18:03.874 --> 00:18:07.545
If your lady asks for a dance.
how can you say no?

257
00:18:07.628 --> 00:18:09.046
-Thank you. Lars.
-Thank you. Thank you. Lars.

258
00:18:09.130 --> 00:18:10.131
Come on.

259
00:18:11.340 --> 00:18:12.341
All right. all right.

260
00:18:12.425 --> 00:18:14.176
If it takes all night

261
00:18:15.886 --> 00:18:17.430
That'll be all right

262
00:18:18.723 --> 00:18:22.476
If I can get you to smile
Before I leave...

263
00:18:44.540 --> 00:18:45.916
Are you taking care of yourself?

264
00:18:46.876 --> 00:18:48.919
Yeah... yeah.

265
00:19:01.265 --> 00:19:04.060
Base. this is Rover One
returning with a full load.

266
00:19:04.143 --> 00:19:05.603
Are we ready to receive the migrants?

267
00:19:05.686 --> 00:19:08.064
Prepare to open
the West Tunnel ramp.

268
00:19:08.147 --> 00:19:09.565
Have the decontamination teams ready.

269
00:19:09.649 --> 00:19:10.816
Copy.

270
00:19:10.900 --> 00:19:12.234
Come on. come on. come on.

271
00:19:14.278 --> 00:19:15.279
Morning. mate.

272
00:19:17.239 --> 00:19:20.701
I was thinking we. uh.
start on the intake pump today. Larsy.

273
00:19:22.662 --> 00:19:23.913
Tackle the rest after lunch?

274
00:19:32.672 --> 00:19:33.673
Shit.

275
00:19:36.384 --> 00:19:38.135
Confirmed personnel incoming...

276
00:19:39.136 --> 00:19:40.346
Copy. Hold. One.

277
00:19:40.429 --> 00:19:42.556
Sir. seeking authorization
for a second trip.

278
00:19:42.640 --> 00:19:44.350
They left a lot of people behind.

279
00:19:44.433 --> 00:19:45.434
A second trip?

280
00:19:49.021 --> 00:19:51.232
-No way.
-Before we make any decisions.

281
00:19:51.315 --> 00:19:53.317
let's just figure out exactly
what we're talking about.

282
00:19:53.401 --> 00:19:55.486
Weren't we discussing limited resources?

283
00:19:56.195 --> 00:19:57.530
Where are they going to sleep?

284
00:19:57.613 --> 00:19:59.073
In your bed?

285
00:19:59.156 --> 00:20:01.617
If it's gonna save lives. yes.

286
00:20:01.701 --> 00:20:03.786
...approach... now.

287
00:20:03.869 --> 00:20:05.663
Uh. bad copy. Rover One. Repeat.

288
00:20:05.746 --> 00:20:07.581
We don't have much time...
Are we approved?

289
00:20:07.665 --> 00:20:08.916
Hold tight.

290
00:20:09.792 --> 00:20:11.460
A reading on that...

291
00:20:11.544 --> 00:20:13.003
Rover One. repeat.

292
00:20:13.087 --> 00:20:14.255
Oh. Jesus!

293
00:20:25.224 --> 00:20:26.350
Oh!

294
00:20:48.330 --> 00:20:50.124
Lars. Lars... Lars. help me.

295
00:21:00.676 --> 00:21:01.844
You all right?

296
00:21:01.927 --> 00:21:03.721
-Attention all personnel...
-Yeah.

297
00:21:10.603 --> 00:21:12.271
Allison!

298
00:21:12.354 --> 00:21:13.355
Allison!

299
00:21:17.067 --> 00:21:19.570
Allison. you okay?

300
00:21:19.653 --> 00:21:21.530
There you go. All right. You hurt?

301
00:21:23.449 --> 00:21:24.742
Okay. You all right?

302
00:21:24.825 --> 00:21:26.035
-Yeah...
-Let's get you up.

303
00:21:26.118 --> 00:21:27.578
Let's get...

304
00:21:30.372 --> 00:21:32.333
-Nathan... Nathan!
-We've gotta go. Now.

305
00:21:37.338 --> 00:21:38.380
-Do you see him?
-No.

306
00:21:39.757 --> 00:21:41.175
Nathan!

307
00:21:41.258 --> 00:21:42.259
Dad!

308
00:21:43.260 --> 00:21:44.804
-I can't breathe.
-Are you hurt?

309
00:21:44.887 --> 00:21:46.680
-You can breathe.
-We've gotta get out of here!

310
00:21:46.764 --> 00:21:48.224
Yeah. let's pack our bags!

311
00:21:48.307 --> 00:21:49.517
Food. clothes. Everything we've got.

312
00:21:49.600 --> 00:21:50.601
-Okay.
-All right. Nathan?

313
00:21:50.684 --> 00:21:52.895
I need you to be with me. kiddo.
You've got this. Nathan.

314
00:21:52.978 --> 00:21:54.104
Help your mum. Pack your stuff.

315
00:21:54.188 --> 00:21:55.564
All right. I'm gonna go get some masks.

316
00:21:56.565 --> 00:21:57.566
Pack your stuff.

317
00:21:57.650 --> 00:22:00.027
Take everything you need.
Get your insulin.

318
00:22:00.110 --> 00:22:02.947
As much as you can
and you put it all in the bag. okay?

319
00:22:03.030 --> 00:22:04.281
We're not coming back.

320
00:22:15.417 --> 00:22:17.628
Jacket. clothes...
anything that'll fit in there.

321
00:22:20.172 --> 00:22:23.050
Okay. I've got some masks. There you go.

322
00:22:23.676 --> 00:22:25.678
Right. put this on. Right. kiddo. Yep.

323
00:22:34.061 --> 00:22:35.271
-You good?
-Yeah. I'm good.

324
00:22:35.354 --> 00:22:36.355
You good?

325
00:22:44.280 --> 00:22:45.322
Let's go!

326
00:22:52.538 --> 00:22:53.873
I'm stuck!

327
00:22:53.956 --> 00:22:55.207
We're not gonna get through here!

328
00:22:55.291 --> 00:22:57.418
-Where are we gonna go?
-To the East Tunnel!

329
00:22:57.501 --> 00:22:58.586
Shit! Go. go!

330
00:23:04.884 --> 00:23:06.302
It's collapsed!

331
00:23:06.385 --> 00:23:08.470
We don't have any other choice!

332
00:23:18.230 --> 00:23:19.356
-John?
-Allison!

333
00:23:19.440 --> 00:23:21.525
-It's falling down!
-I've got you! Come on!

334
00:23:22.526 --> 00:23:23.736
All right. you're good.

335
00:23:23.819 --> 00:23:25.529
Come on. we've gotta go. we've gotta go!

336
00:23:26.780 --> 00:23:27.907
Come on. come on!

337
00:23:30.367 --> 00:23:32.411
Okay. are we covered up
as much as possible?

338
00:23:32.494 --> 00:23:34.038
-Yes.
-Check your masks!

339
00:23:34.121 --> 00:23:35.247
Everything's good.

340
00:23:46.258 --> 00:23:47.635
Go. go. go!

341
00:23:58.395 --> 00:24:01.398
-The radiation. what do we do?
-We've gotta get off this island.

342
00:24:01.482 --> 00:24:03.067
This way. to the beach.

343
00:24:18.874 --> 00:24:20.709
Nathan! Where's Nathan?

344
00:24:21.835 --> 00:24:23.003
Where'd he go?

345
00:24:23.087 --> 00:24:25.172
-Nathan!
-Mom. Dad. over here!

346
00:24:25.255 --> 00:24:26.256
There!

347
00:24:28.175 --> 00:24:29.176
Dr. Amina!

348
00:24:29.259 --> 00:24:30.928
-You okay?
-Dr. Casey?

349
00:24:31.011 --> 00:24:32.972
Can you stand?

350
00:24:33.055 --> 00:24:34.348
Come on. let's get up.

351
00:24:34.431 --> 00:24:36.558
There's lifeboats
on the beach. Let's go. Let's go!

352
00:25:00.040 --> 00:25:01.792
All right. make sure to follow me!

353
00:25:02.418 --> 00:25:03.961
There are more boats
at the end of the beach!

354
00:25:10.175 --> 00:25:11.176
Come on!

355
00:25:20.728 --> 00:25:21.770
Help!

356
00:25:22.521 --> 00:25:23.856
Help!

357
00:25:23.939 --> 00:25:24.940
-Just give it.
-No!

358
00:25:25.983 --> 00:25:27.192
John! Over here!

359
00:25:27.276 --> 00:25:28.360
Allison!

360
00:25:29.069 --> 00:25:30.946
Stop! Let him go!

361
00:25:39.913 --> 00:25:40.914
Stay back!

362
00:25:42.666 --> 00:25:44.626
There's one more! Come on!

363
00:25:44.710 --> 00:25:46.587
There's one more over there!

364
00:25:47.671 --> 00:25:49.465
Hurry!

365
00:25:51.341 --> 00:25:52.342
Come on!

366
00:25:56.388 --> 00:25:58.140
We've gotta go. Come on!

367
00:25:59.725 --> 00:26:00.934
We've gotta go now!

368
00:26:01.018 --> 00:26:02.811
Okay! Go. go. go!

369
00:26:03.979 --> 00:26:05.689
No more! Shut the door!

370
00:26:05.773 --> 00:26:07.107
No! Let them in! We can make room!

371
00:26:07.191 --> 00:26:09.026
No more! We'll capsize like the others!

372
00:26:09.109 --> 00:26:10.611
Secure the hatch!

373
00:26:10.694 --> 00:26:13.072
-We can't take any more. I'm sorry!
-Don't leave us!

374
00:26:33.842 --> 00:26:35.135
You okay? All right.

375
00:26:38.097 --> 00:26:40.307
Wait! Wait! No!

376
00:26:41.266 --> 00:26:43.685
All right. everybody okay?

377
00:26:48.107 --> 00:26:49.858
Dad! Dad!

378
00:26:49.942 --> 00:26:52.027
Oh. my God! Oh. my God!

379
00:26:52.111 --> 00:26:53.654
Everybody. hold on!

380
00:27:11.922 --> 00:27:12.923
Oh. my God!

381
00:27:17.219 --> 00:27:19.096
Brace! Brace!

382
00:27:45.914 --> 00:27:47.583
You okay. Nathan?

383
00:27:47.666 --> 00:27:48.917
I'm good.

384
00:27:49.001 --> 00:27:50.085
It's gone.

385
00:27:51.086 --> 00:27:52.087
It's all gone.

386
00:28:27.080 --> 00:28:30.417
Hey. I think the air
quality's good. Better.

387
00:28:30.500 --> 00:28:32.085
-We can take off the masks?
-Yeah.

388
00:28:43.263 --> 00:28:44.806
-You all right?
-Yeah.

389
00:28:44.890 --> 00:28:47.392
-Let me see you.
-Where do we go?

390
00:28:48.352 --> 00:28:49.728
There's nothing to go back to.

391
00:28:50.771 --> 00:28:52.606
Isn't Iceland the closest place to here?

392
00:28:52.689 --> 00:28:54.274
Ice... Iceland's gone.

393
00:28:55.067 --> 00:28:56.693
Well. we need a destination.

394
00:28:57.277 --> 00:28:58.695
We just need to hit land.

395
00:28:58.779 --> 00:29:00.822
Clarke changed the direction
of the current.

396
00:29:00.906 --> 00:29:02.616
It's now flowing south.

397
00:29:02.699 --> 00:29:05.911
We have with us barely
a week's supply of MREs and water.

398
00:29:05.994 --> 00:29:08.330
[. uh... Europe is probably our best bet.

399
00:29:08.413 --> 00:29:11.750
So. that's good. Then we head southeast.

400
00:29:12.334 --> 00:29:13.710
Until we reach England.

401
00:29:13.794 --> 00:29:16.004
If we can get to London.
we can go to Mackenzie's.

402
00:29:17.339 --> 00:29:19.633
Perfect.
Should take less than a week.

403
00:29:20.259 --> 00:29:21.301
Pray we make it.

404
00:29:23.178 --> 00:29:24.221
Southeast.

405
00:30:02.342 --> 00:30:03.343
Okay.

406
00:30:04.094 --> 00:30:05.095
Try it now?

407
00:30:12.477 --> 00:30:14.271
All right.
Let me try one more thing.

408
00:30:14.354 --> 00:30:16.064
Okay.

409
00:30:19.151 --> 00:30:20.986
There she goes.

410
00:30:34.791 --> 00:30:36.668
How many fragments
do you think are up there?

411
00:30:39.921 --> 00:30:41.840
More than I can count. that's for sure.

412
00:30:42.924 --> 00:30:44.551
And so at least 50.

413
00:30:48.138 --> 00:30:50.432
Whoa. That's Andromeda.

414
00:30:50.515 --> 00:30:52.601
-That's a whole other galaxy.
-Wow.

415
00:30:54.061 --> 00:30:56.188
I can't believe
I'm seeing the stars for real.

416
00:30:57.397 --> 00:30:58.815
It's pretty cool. huh?

417
00:31:00.359 --> 00:31:01.902
I hope you never lose that.

418
00:31:03.403 --> 00:31:05.489
That... wonder of yours.

419
00:31:15.624 --> 00:31:17.501
I wonder where that's gonna hit.

420
00:31:34.768 --> 00:31:36.228
I'll take a look.

421
00:31:36.311 --> 00:31:37.521
It's not that.

422
00:31:39.106 --> 00:31:40.315
We're outta gas.

423
00:31:41.233 --> 00:31:42.526
And maybe we can ration...

424
00:31:43.276 --> 00:31:45.070
two more days of water and MREs.

425
00:31:46.279 --> 00:31:47.864
We're at the mercy of the current now.

426
00:31:53.120 --> 00:31:54.913
So wait. where did you end up then?

427
00:31:54.996 --> 00:31:57.165
-We ended in Shenandoah.
-Really?

428
00:31:57.249 --> 00:31:58.959
Oh. you know. I've always
wanted to go there.

429
00:31:59.042 --> 00:32:00.085
-Yeah. it was great.
-Was it?

430
00:32:00.168 --> 00:32:02.671
My wife wanted to do the whole trip.
but I ended up cutting it short

431
00:32:02.754 --> 00:32:04.381
so I could take a new job.

432
00:32:04.464 --> 00:32:07.426
Seemed like a big deal at the time.

433
00:32:08.051 --> 00:32:09.469
Your wife.

434
00:32:09.553 --> 00:32:11.263
Did you lose her leaving the bunker?

435
00:32:12.472 --> 00:32:14.850
No. I lost her getting... getting to it.

436
00:32:30.407 --> 00:32:31.408
Need some...

437
00:32:32.033 --> 00:32:33.326
Oh. I need food.

438
00:32:36.663 --> 00:32:37.664
Crater.

439
00:32:38.373 --> 00:32:40.000
The crater has enough...

440
00:32:40.083 --> 00:32:42.085
Build a bunker. and...

441
00:32:43.420 --> 00:32:44.421
Swim...

442
00:32:44.504 --> 00:32:46.214
We need to make it.

443
00:32:57.392 --> 00:32:59.811
-Oh. my God. What did we hit?
-Oh. my God!

444
00:32:59.895 --> 00:33:02.230
It's land. guys.
What is that?

445
00:33:02.314 --> 00:33:03.440
We've hit land!

446
00:33:10.071 --> 00:33:11.406
That's the Liver Building.

447
00:33:12.032 --> 00:33:13.033
We're in Liverpool!

448
00:33:13.116 --> 00:33:14.117
-What?
-England!

449
00:33:15.368 --> 00:33:16.369
What?

450
00:33:16.453 --> 00:33:19.122
-What?
-In England? Oh. my God!

451
00:33:22.250 --> 00:33:24.127
The air's okay. for now.

452
00:33:25.337 --> 00:33:27.339
We'll need to find shelter.

453
00:33:27.422 --> 00:33:28.465
What did we hit?

454
00:33:39.768 --> 00:33:41.019
Oh. my God.

455
00:33:42.354 --> 00:33:44.064
Here. we're on a... we're on a building top.

456
00:33:44.147 --> 00:33:45.941
Let's get these oars and push us off.

457
00:33:49.528 --> 00:33:51.613
-You ready?
-Yeah.

458
00:33:57.869 --> 00:33:59.913
There's a road up ahead. Lieutenant.

459
00:34:00.413 --> 00:34:02.332
-Can you steer us round that way?
-Okay.

460
00:34:22.310 --> 00:34:23.770
-Dan. you reverse.
-Yeah.

461
00:34:23.853 --> 00:34:25.397
-With the paddle.
-Yeah. got it.

462
00:34:35.865 --> 00:34:37.075
Oh. there we go.

463
00:34:42.080 --> 00:34:43.373
All right. let's go.

464
00:34:45.125 --> 00:34:46.126
Stay close.

465
00:34:46.209 --> 00:34:47.752
We don't know what's out there.

466
00:34:50.589 --> 00:34:52.215
Come on. kiddo. Good stuff.

467
00:35:01.766 --> 00:35:04.185
It looks. uh. abandoned.

468
00:35:04.269 --> 00:35:06.313
All right. first thing's first.

469
00:35:06.396 --> 00:35:08.648
we need to find some food and water.

470
00:35:08.732 --> 00:35:11.776
And we can't stay up here the whole time.

471
00:35:12.277 --> 00:35:14.112
SO a proper place
for everybody to shelter.

472
00:35:14.195 --> 00:35:16.489
Wasn't there a bomb shelter
or a bunker in this area?

473
00:35:16.573 --> 00:35:19.242
Yeah. but we've never had
any contact with them.

474
00:35:19.326 --> 00:35:21.369
Still. we should try to find it.

475
00:35:22.787 --> 00:35:24.456
Oh. look. there's people there.

476
00:35:34.382 --> 00:35:35.634
Where are they?

477
00:35:36.509 --> 00:35:38.887
Where are your politicians?

478
00:35:39.471 --> 00:35:41.222
Your noble kings?

479
00:35:42.682 --> 00:35:44.851
They are all underground.

480
00:35:47.354 --> 00:35:49.022
Only the true God...

481
00:35:49.773 --> 00:35:51.107
How do they live outside?

482
00:35:51.191 --> 00:35:52.651
...since the beginning of time...

483
00:35:52.734 --> 00:35:54.194
They probably don't have a choice.

484
00:35:55.487 --> 00:35:57.197
But they can't survive for long.

485
00:35:58.865 --> 00:36:00.617
There's more people that way.

486
00:36:04.120 --> 00:36:06.706
No badges!
Clearance badges only!

487
00:36:07.540 --> 00:36:09.668
No badges! No entry!

488
00:36:10.543 --> 00:36:12.128
Clearance badges only!

489
00:36:13.296 --> 00:36:15.173
Clearance badges only!

490
00:36:15.256 --> 00:36:16.508
We have badges!

491
00:36:16.591 --> 00:36:18.426
Hey. hey. hey. hey! Hey!

492
00:36:19.260 --> 00:36:21.721
We're governing officials
from Greenland Station!

493
00:36:21.805 --> 00:36:23.932
And we're requesting emergency asylum!

494
00:36:24.015 --> 00:36:25.350
Give me your clearance badges!

495
00:36:25.433 --> 00:36:26.810
-Badges.
-Here. Here.

496
00:36:29.354 --> 00:36:31.231
She's clear. Come through.

497
00:36:31.314 --> 00:36:33.983
I can't find my badge!
I can't find my badge.

498
00:36:35.151 --> 00:36:36.861
Then that's it! Just her!

499
00:36:36.945 --> 00:36:38.571
Listen! Listen. they're with us!

500
00:36:38.655 --> 00:36:40.490
One badge! One entry!

501
00:36:42.117 --> 00:36:43.284
We're Allison's family!

502
00:36:43.368 --> 00:36:44.536
My name's Adam Shaw!

503
00:36:44.619 --> 00:36:46.037
Move back!

504
00:36:46.121 --> 00:36:47.622
I'm from Thule bunker in Greenland.

505
00:36:47.706 --> 00:36:50.917
Just run me in your system!

506
00:36:52.919 --> 00:36:55.630
I'm a governing official!
My name's Adam Shaw!

507
00:36:55.714 --> 00:36:58.967
You should find me in your system!
I'm a governing official from...

508
00:37:00.635 --> 00:37:02.053
Oh. Christ!

509
00:37:02.137 --> 00:37:03.138
Let us in!

510
00:37:04.889 --> 00:37:07.434
-Back up!
-Close the gates!

511
00:37:07.517 --> 00:37:09.978
What have you done?

512
00:37:10.061 --> 00:37:12.105
Adam? Adam!

513
00:37:14.232 --> 00:37:16.151
What's happening?

514
00:37:20.280 --> 00:37:22.574
-Move! Move!
-Move! Move!

515
00:37:22.657 --> 00:37:23.992
We've gotta go.
We've gotta get out of here!

516
00:37:24.075 --> 00:37:25.160
Let's go! We've gotta go!

517
00:37:26.202 --> 00:37:28.913
All right. okay. Casey. come on.

518
00:37:28.997 --> 00:37:30.874
-Casey!
-We've gotta go! He's gone!

519
00:37:30.957 --> 00:37:33.251
Whoa. whoa. whoa! Yo. yo. yo. yo. yo. yo!

520
00:37:33.334 --> 00:37:34.961
Wait! No. no. no. no. no. no. no!

521
00:37:35.044 --> 00:37:36.379
Wait. wait. wait. wait!

522
00:37:36.463 --> 00:37:38.006
-What? Move. my friend!
-We need a ride.

523
00:37:38.089 --> 00:37:39.090
I need to go.

524
00:37:39.174 --> 00:37:40.633
Oh. you've gotta take our family. please.

525
00:37:40.717 --> 00:37:42.594
-Where?
-Uh. London. London.

526
00:37:42.677 --> 00:37:43.887
-London! Mackenzie's.
-Okay. London.

527
00:37:43.970 --> 00:37:46.681
-You have to give me something.
-We don't have anything!

528
00:37:46.765 --> 00:37:47.891
That will do.

529
00:37:49.142 --> 00:37:50.894
-Enter.
-Go. go. go. go!

530
00:37:50.977 --> 00:37:52.145
All right. there you go.

531
00:38:12.207 --> 00:38:13.208
Thank you.

532
00:38:14.918 --> 00:38:17.420
Oh. my God. Oh. my God!

533
00:38:23.134 --> 00:38:24.844
Oh. my God.

534
00:38:28.097 --> 00:38:30.058
Hey. Hey. hey. hey. hey. look at me.

535
00:38:31.434 --> 00:38:32.936
It's okay. it's okay.

536
00:38:33.019 --> 00:38:34.813
It's all right. Okay. Deep breaths.

537
00:38:38.024 --> 00:38:39.234
We're gonna go to Mac's.

538
00:38:40.068 --> 00:38:41.694
Everything is gonna be okay.

539
00:38:42.612 --> 00:38:43.613
Okay?

540
00:38:45.532 --> 00:38:47.200
Is everywhere like this?

541
00:38:49.661 --> 00:38:51.496
The world is a dangerous place now.

542
00:38:52.997 --> 00:38:56.042
People are so desperate.
they'll kill you for a scrap of food.

543
00:38:57.335 --> 00:38:59.045
A radiation storm like that one.

544
00:38:59.712 --> 00:39:01.464
they come out of nowhere.

545
00:39:01.548 --> 00:39:02.632
Kill you in seconds.

546
00:39:03.550 --> 00:39:04.884
And if they don't get you quick.

547
00:39:05.635 --> 00:39:07.679
you'll die a slow death anyway.

548
00:39:08.930 --> 00:39:09.931
Hmm.

549
00:39:11.724 --> 00:39:12.725
Yeah.

550
00:39:14.102 --> 00:39:17.188
Great. The air filtration in here.
how is it?

551
00:39:17.272 --> 00:39:18.273
It works.

552
00:39:18.356 --> 00:39:21.067
but none of us are living
to a hundred. my friend.

553
00:39:24.863 --> 00:39:27.365
Babe. when was the last time
you spoke to Mackenzie?

554
00:39:27.448 --> 00:39:30.326
Um. eight or nine months ago.

555
00:39:54.809 --> 00:39:55.894
Dr. Amina?

556
00:39:57.395 --> 00:40:00.273
Do you believe it's real? The crater?

557
00:40:01.065 --> 00:40:02.650
Yeah. I believe it's possible.

558
00:40:04.527 --> 00:40:09.073
So it is just like
the dinosaurs. the K-T event.

559
00:40:10.199 --> 00:40:12.243
Nathan. do you know what
happened after the K-T event?

560
00:40:12.327 --> 00:40:13.828
Life came back.

561
00:40:13.912 --> 00:40:16.331
Not just came back. It flourished.

562
00:40:17.707 --> 00:40:21.210
The impact created the seeds for new life.

563
00:40:21.294 --> 00:40:23.630
Without the K-T event.
we wouldn't even be here.

564
00:40:26.299 --> 00:40:27.675
We are close.

565
00:40:28.301 --> 00:40:30.637
Maybe another half hour to London.

566
00:40:30.720 --> 00:40:32.221
Let's make this quick.

567
00:40:32.305 --> 00:40:34.474
Don't wanna spend too long outside.

568
00:40:43.483 --> 00:40:44.484
What's your name?

569
00:40:46.194 --> 00:40:47.195
Obi.

570
00:40:48.112 --> 00:40:49.197
Where are you from. Obi?

571
00:40:49.906 --> 00:40:50.907
Nigeria.

572
00:40:51.908 --> 00:40:53.034
Right.

573
00:40:53.117 --> 00:40:55.119
I moved to England 12 years ago.

574
00:40:56.788 --> 00:40:58.373
I used to hear about life here.

575
00:40:59.999 --> 00:41:02.335
It was a childish dream of mine.

576
00:41:02.919 --> 00:41:05.004
Well. I'm sorry this
is what you got instead.

577
00:41:05.088 --> 00:41:06.589
No. I still love it here.

578
00:41:07.966 --> 00:41:09.050
It's become my second wife.

579
00:41:10.593 --> 00:41:12.011
Though sometimes I do wonder...

580
00:41:13.429 --> 00:41:14.889
what it would be like to go back.

581
00:41:16.015 --> 00:41:18.142
If I'd still recognize anything at all.

582
00:41:20.603 --> 00:41:21.604
Mmm.

583
00:41:22.271 --> 00:41:25.024
What do you hear about people
heading further south.

584
00:41:25.108 --> 00:41:26.651
over into France?

585
00:41:29.737 --> 00:41:31.322
France is more dangerous than here.

586
00:41:32.323 --> 00:41:33.908
Is that because of what's over there?

587
00:41:33.992 --> 00:41:36.828
You mean the stuff your scientist friend
there was talking about?

588
00:41:37.412 --> 00:41:39.497
-Yeah.
-Sounds nice.

589
00:41:39.580 --> 00:41:41.958
Also sounds like ashi gi.

590
00:41:44.585 --> 00:41:45.670
Bullshit.

591
00:41:51.634 --> 00:41:52.844
You good?

592
00:41:52.927 --> 00:41:54.137
Yeah.

593
00:42:05.940 --> 00:42:06.983
Whoa. what is that?

594
00:42:07.817 --> 00:42:08.818
Another storm?

595
00:42:08.901 --> 00:42:10.319
No. that's not a storm.

596
00:42:18.703 --> 00:42:21.789
Allison! Grab onto something!

597
00:42:23.124 --> 00:42:24.917
Come. come!

598
00:42:27.503 --> 00:42:29.130
There.

599
00:42:57.700 --> 00:42:59.077
Obi! No!

600
00:42:59.160 --> 00:43:00.244
It's all I have!

601
00:43:21.140 --> 00:43:23.309
-You okay?
-Yeah.

602
00:44:17.530 --> 00:44:18.865
I hope she's still here.

603
00:44:25.121 --> 00:44:27.373
-Mac!
-Oh. sh...

604
00:44:28.791 --> 00:44:31.544
Bloody hell! Bloody...

605
00:44:31.627 --> 00:44:33.504
-Get inside! Come!
-Mac!

606
00:44:33.588 --> 00:44:35.256
-Get inside!
-Is that loaded?

607
00:44:35.339 --> 00:44:37.216
-Oh!
-Hi.

608
00:44:37.300 --> 00:44:38.426
Get inside!

609
00:44:40.511 --> 00:44:43.556
How are you on my doorstep right now?

610
00:44:43.639 --> 00:44:46.017
I haven't heard from you for so long!

611
00:44:46.100 --> 00:44:47.727
I was beginning to fear the worst.

612
00:44:47.810 --> 00:44:52.607
Oh. and John! I never thought
I'd see that ugly mug again!

613
00:44:52.690 --> 00:44:53.733
-Oh...
-You're looking good. Mac.

614
00:44:53.816 --> 00:44:55.484
Oh. liar.

615
00:44:55.568 --> 00:44:57.945
Oh. this must be the man. yes!

616
00:44:58.029 --> 00:45:00.406
You're all your mum ever talks about!

617
00:45:00.489 --> 00:45:01.616
-Really?
-Yeah.

618
00:45:01.699 --> 00:45:03.659
Nearly all. I think.

619
00:45:03.743 --> 00:45:05.828
Honestly. I can't believe
my eyes.

620
00:45:06.621 --> 00:45:09.498
Oh. wow.
You're celebrating Christmas early.

621
00:45:09.582 --> 00:45:11.542
Oh. every day is Christmas here.

622
00:45:11.626 --> 00:45:13.711
Here. just put your bags down anywhere

623
00:45:13.794 --> 00:45:15.004
and just make yourselves at home.

624
00:45:15.087 --> 00:45:17.173
Honestly. I can't believe...

625
00:45:17.256 --> 00:45:21.469
Um. also the air is really
a lot better than the outside.

626
00:45:21.552 --> 00:45:24.138
I managed to seal off
this wing of the hospital

627
00:45:24.222 --> 00:45:28.142
and the generator keeps
the filtration system going.

628
00:45:28.851 --> 00:45:30.978
It's not as good as the air
you're used to in the bunkers.

629
00:45:31.062 --> 00:45:33.231
but it'll give us a few more years.

630
00:45:33.314 --> 00:45:34.440
-Thank you.
-Please. no.

631
00:45:34.523 --> 00:45:35.816
You're family. honestly.

632
00:45:35.900 --> 00:45:38.694
I mean. I dream about our time
in the States.

633
00:45:38.778 --> 00:45:40.279
Those American boys.

634
00:45:40.363 --> 00:45:42.406
They're suckers for an accent.

635
00:45:42.490 --> 00:45:44.408
Ah. So are the girls.

636
00:45:46.702 --> 00:45:48.913
-Hey.
-What are you treating here?

637
00:45:48.996 --> 00:45:52.208
Oh. Alzheimer's. And. well. broken hearts.

638
00:45:52.291 --> 00:45:54.502
Most of them have no idea
what happened to their families

639
00:45:54.585 --> 00:45:55.836
or anything about the comet.

640
00:45:56.420 --> 00:45:57.505
Which is probably just as well.

641
00:45:58.673 --> 00:45:59.674
So I stayed on.

642
00:45:59.757 --> 00:46:02.176
Even when the government
stopped delivering food

643
00:46:02.260 --> 00:46:03.719
and the lights turned off.

644
00:46:04.345 --> 00:46:06.847
I won't let them be abandoned again.

645
00:46:09.141 --> 00:46:11.727
Actually. speaking of which.
it's time I prepped their supper.

646
00:46:11.811 --> 00:46:12.812
Oh. well. I'll help.

647
00:46:12.895 --> 00:46:14.355
Oh. that's so kind. Thank you.

648
00:46:14.438 --> 00:46:16.649
Hey. John. um. you and Nathan
grab some more coals.

649
00:46:16.732 --> 00:46:19.151
I feel like celebrating!

650
00:46:24.907 --> 00:46:27.159
Run back in. Oh. my God. just...

651
00:46:27.243 --> 00:46:28.577
Whoa. it's amazing!

652
00:46:28.661 --> 00:46:29.954
Okay. How's this?

653
00:46:31.706 --> 00:46:33.541
See? That's still better.

654
00:46:33.624 --> 00:46:36.711
We finally spoke. this is finally...

655
00:46:38.045 --> 00:46:40.047
-Cheers everybody.
-Cheers!

656
00:46:42.758 --> 00:46:45.177
Guys. this almost feels normal. Almost.

657
00:46:45.261 --> 00:46:47.054
Yeah. Almost.

658
00:46:52.268 --> 00:46:53.519
Oh. he's still sleeping?

659
00:46:54.186 --> 00:46:56.897
Ah. that's good. Poor kid is exhausted.

660
00:46:57.606 --> 00:46:59.358
Does he remember the impact at all?

661
00:46:59.442 --> 00:47:00.443
Yeah. he does.

662
00:47:00.526 --> 00:47:02.820
I was hoping he would forget
with time. but he hasn't.

663
00:47:02.903 --> 00:47:05.614
He's just... I guess he's still processing.

664
00:47:05.698 --> 00:47:07.700
God. you can't put Clarke in a box.

665
00:47:07.783 --> 00:47:10.077
Not when you're reminded
of it every time you look out the window.

666
00:47:10.703 --> 00:47:13.706
What do you know. Mac. about the crater?

667
00:47:14.290 --> 00:47:16.834
You know. the... where Clarke hit?

668
00:47:17.752 --> 00:47:19.295
Are you thinking of buying a holiday home?

669
00:47:21.297 --> 00:47:23.424
No. I've just heard rumors.
just a load of rumors.

670
00:47:24.050 --> 00:47:26.385
No. because Casey thinks
there's a possibility

671
00:47:26.469 --> 00:47:27.553
life returned there. right?

672
00:47:27.636 --> 00:47:29.513
Yeah. I do. Yeah.

673
00:47:29.597 --> 00:47:32.683
Let's say you have extremely
high temperatures. right?

674
00:47:33.934 --> 00:47:37.104
And you added in raw materials and. uh.

675
00:47:37.188 --> 00:47:39.315
the ocean water from the tsunami.

676
00:47:39.398 --> 00:47:41.233
Throw in some terrigenous nutrients

677
00:47:41.317 --> 00:47:43.194
from the rocks smashed during impact.

678
00:47:43.277 --> 00:47:46.072
then it's possible you could. uh...

679
00:47:46.822 --> 00:47:49.158
You could create the building
blocks for new life.

680
00:47:50.326 --> 00:47:51.452
Mmm.

681
00:47:52.244 --> 00:47:53.454
Breathable air.

682
00:47:54.955 --> 00:47:57.375
Drinkable water. It's... it's possible.

683
00:47:58.876 --> 00:48:00.878
That's a nice thought.

684
00:48:00.961 --> 00:48:06.300
But. um. you know. what I've made here is.

685
00:48:06.384 --> 00:48:09.428
it's good enough to survive these days.

686
00:48:10.137 --> 00:48:11.764
And it's safe. you know?

687
00:48:11.847 --> 00:48:13.015
I've made it safe.

688
00:48:15.184 --> 00:48:19.230
Oh... Okay. safer than outside.

689
00:48:19.313 --> 00:48:20.898
Hey!

690
00:48:20.981 --> 00:48:22.608
London isn't London anymore.

691
00:48:46.507 --> 00:48:48.426
-John. are you okay?
-Yeah. yeah.

692
00:48:49.093 --> 00:48:51.053
-Oh. my God. you're bleeding.
-Yeah.

693
00:48:52.012 --> 00:48:53.431
Yeah. Must be the air.

694
00:48:54.014 --> 00:48:55.057
Nosebleed.

695
00:48:55.891 --> 00:48:57.143
John...

696
00:48:59.186 --> 00:49:00.187
What's going on?

697
00:49:01.397 --> 00:49:02.940
Just... I've got a nosebleed.

698
00:49:07.236 --> 00:49:08.237
Bullshit.

699
00:49:11.031 --> 00:49:12.408
The doctor said. um...

700
00:49:13.492 --> 00:49:16.412
when symptoms start... bleeding...

701
00:49:18.497 --> 00:49:19.748
six to eight weeks.

702
00:49:26.630 --> 00:49:28.549
Six weeks? What?

703
00:49:28.632 --> 00:49:29.675
I mean. it may be more. I...

704
00:49:29.758 --> 00:49:32.303
What are you talking about?
That can't be right.

705
00:49:32.386 --> 00:49:34.930
We're here now. with Mac.
She has medicine.

706
00:49:35.014 --> 00:49:36.557
I'm sure we can get
you the right medication.

707
00:49:36.640 --> 00:49:38.392
-Ali. no. Ali...
-And everything will be okay.

708
00:49:38.476 --> 00:49:39.602
Al .

709
00:49:42.271 --> 00:49:43.481
It's not fixable.

710
00:49:44.690 --> 00:49:46.066
What do you mean?

711
00:49:49.778 --> 00:49:50.779
It's...

712
00:49:53.032 --> 00:49:54.617
Too many trips outside. I guess.

713
00:49:56.160 --> 00:49:57.578
Why didn't you tell me?

714
00:49:58.204 --> 00:49:59.538
-I wanted to...
-John!

715
00:49:59.622 --> 00:50:01.123
I wanted to...

716
00:50:01.207 --> 00:50:03.459
-Why?
-Because I couldn't see this...

717
00:50:03.542 --> 00:50:05.794
I couldn't see this from you. I couldn't...

718
00:50:05.878 --> 00:50:08.506
Okay. all right.
Okay. okay. okay.

719
00:50:10.633 --> 00:50:11.634
Look at me.

720
00:50:12.885 --> 00:50:13.886
Okay.

721
00:50:15.179 --> 00:50:18.974
Okay. We're gonna stay here. with Mac.

722
00:50:19.892 --> 00:50:21.810
And we're gonna take
this time that we have left

723
00:50:21.894 --> 00:50:25.356
and we're gonna be together as a family.

724
00:50:25.439 --> 00:50:27.066
We can't stay here. Ali.

725
00:50:27.149 --> 00:50:28.317
I don't wanna stay here.

726
00:50:29.026 --> 00:50:30.319
I don't wanna die here.

727
00:50:31.737 --> 00:50:33.572
I don't want you and Nathan to live here.

728
00:50:33.656 --> 00:50:36.575
We didn't come all this way for this!

729
00:50:37.826 --> 00:50:39.578
I mean. what if Casey's right?

730
00:50:40.579 --> 00:50:41.747
About the crater.

731
00:50:42.790 --> 00:50:48.629
There's something there.
like a fresh. a new beginning.

732
00:50:48.712 --> 00:50:50.839
For you. For our son.

733
00:50:50.923 --> 00:50:53.884
Half of his life has been surviving.

734
00:50:54.426 --> 00:50:56.720
We have to get Nathan to the crater.

735
00:50:56.804 --> 00:50:57.805
I know.

736
00:50:58.639 --> 00:51:00.057
There's no life for him here.

737
00:51:02.768 --> 00:51:04.728
-Okay.
-Okay.

738
00:51:13.487 --> 00:51:15.864
You're sure you're okay
with us taking this?

739
00:51:15.948 --> 00:51:17.825
Oh. well. I took it
from someone else.

740
00:51:17.908 --> 00:51:20.119
And it should have enough fuel
to get you to the Channel.

741
00:51:20.202 --> 00:51:21.704
-Yeah.
-Take this.

742
00:51:21.787 --> 00:51:23.789
And don't stop for anyone.

743
00:51:24.415 --> 00:51:26.417
You're gonna wanna head
down through Dover.

744
00:51:26.917 --> 00:51:29.128
It's the only place you'll
be able to cross the Channel.

745
00:51:29.211 --> 00:51:30.212
Thank you.

746
00:51:31.255 --> 00:51:32.256
Oh...

747
00:51:32.339 --> 00:51:33.591
Okay.

748
00:51:37.845 --> 00:51:39.430
-Take care of my girl!
- I will.

749
00:51:39.513 --> 00:51:41.432
Oh. Nate...

750
00:51:43.058 --> 00:51:44.685
-Nice to meet you.
-Bye. Nate.

751
00:52:07.875 --> 00:52:10.961
Okay.
So according to this map.

752
00:52:11.045 --> 00:52:13.255
we should get there in about two hours.

753
00:52:19.136 --> 00:52:20.220
You're very quiet there. bud.

754
00:52:21.972 --> 00:52:23.807
You remember we used to play
those car games?

755
00:52:23.891 --> 00:52:25.100
Back when you were little?

756
00:52:25.184 --> 00:52:26.477
Yeah. I remember.

757
00:52:26.560 --> 00:52:28.145
Like "I Spy"...

758
00:52:29.021 --> 00:52:30.689
-"Would You Rather"...
-That was my favorite.

759
00:52:30.773 --> 00:52:31.774
You know. my sister and I.

760
00:52:31.857 --> 00:52:34.193
we used to play 21 Questions
on road trips.

761
00:52:34.276 --> 00:52:36.236
-Do you remember that one?
-Go on. what do you say. Nathan?

762
00:52:36.320 --> 00:52:37.363
-You wanna play?
-No thanks.

763
00:52:37.446 --> 00:52:39.657
You know what? Let's play
anyway. without him.

764
00:52:39.740 --> 00:52:41.659
-Yeah!
-I wanna play I Spy though.

765
00:52:41.742 --> 00:52:43.786
-I'll go first.
-No. I'll go first.

766
00:52:43.869 --> 00:52:45.245
-I'm gonna go first.
-Okay...

767
00:52:50.250 --> 00:52:52.044
-Oh. my...
-Casey.

768
00:52:54.213 --> 00:52:56.632
-Get down. Nathan!
-Nathan. get down! Stay down!

769
00:52:56.715 --> 00:52:58.884
Don't shoot the engine!
We need that car!

770
00:53:00.052 --> 00:53:02.596
-Move forward! Move!
-Who are they?

771
00:53:02.680 --> 00:53:04.973
Marauders! Nathan. stay down!

772
00:53:06.558 --> 00:53:08.727
Ah... Go. go.

773
00:53:41.885 --> 00:53:43.721
It's okay. it's okay.

774
00:53:43.804 --> 00:53:45.597
It's okay. it's okay.

775
00:53:45.681 --> 00:53:48.600
It's okay. it's okay. It's okay.

776
00:53:48.684 --> 00:53:51.019
Nathan? Nathan? Nathan?

777
00:53:52.604 --> 00:53:55.399
Nathan. are you okay? You okay?

778
00:53:56.775 --> 00:53:58.193
Okay. There you go.

779
00:54:34.146 --> 00:54:35.939
May the road rise to meet you.

780
00:54:37.399 --> 00:54:39.443
May the wind be always at your back.

781
00:54:40.694 --> 00:54:42.946
May the sun shine warm upon your face.

782
00:54:44.198 --> 00:54:46.950
And may the rains fall softly
upon your fields.

783
00:54:54.249 --> 00:54:56.668
Why do people say prayers at funerals?

784
00:54:59.004 --> 00:55:01.715
It sounds like you're wishing them well.

785
00:55:02.883 --> 00:55:04.009
And they're dead.

786
00:55:04.092 --> 00:55:06.929
Well. you are... wishing them well.

787
00:55:07.679 --> 00:55:09.056
It's an old tradition.

788
00:55:12.267 --> 00:55:14.645
Same reason they put coins over the eyes.

789
00:55:15.312 --> 00:55:17.272
-Coins?
-Bribe the ferryman.

790
00:55:17.856 --> 00:55:20.317
Crossing the river
to the world of the dead.

791
00:55:23.946 --> 00:55:25.656
Even if they don't believe in Heaven?

792
00:55:33.664 --> 00:55:35.374
Even if they don't believe in Heaven.

793
00:56:06.238 --> 00:56:07.698
Is that the English Channel?

794
00:56:08.991 --> 00:56:10.033
It was.

795
00:56:11.952 --> 00:56:12.953
Jesus.

796
00:56:13.954 --> 00:56:18.208
My dad used to take us over here to France
on a ferry when I was a kid.

797
00:56:18.292 --> 00:56:21.044
-And that was all water?
-Oh. yeah.

798
00:56:21.128 --> 00:56:24.298
Twenty miles of sea from here to France.

799
00:56:24.381 --> 00:56:26.133
There's so many battles.

800
00:56:26.216 --> 00:56:28.218
there's so many wars fought over this.

801
00:56:29.094 --> 00:56:30.178
It's all gone.

802
00:56:32.472 --> 00:56:34.516
Well. at least we don't have
to take a boat.

803
00:56:35.601 --> 00:56:37.477
Exactly.
Let's get across this quick

804
00:56:37.561 --> 00:56:39.104
and find a place for the night.

805
00:57:00.959 --> 00:57:02.628
Is that a Spanish galleon?

806
00:57:29.529 --> 00:57:31.073
What are they all stopped for?

807
00:57:32.824 --> 00:57:33.867
I don't know.

808
00:57:46.713 --> 00:57:47.965
I guess we're leaving the car.

809
00:57:57.557 --> 00:57:59.518
We're gonna cross that?

810
00:58:00.060 --> 00:58:01.895
Yeah. We're gonna have to.

811
00:58:27.004 --> 00:58:28.672
Watch your step now.

812
00:58:28.755 --> 00:58:30.424
-I've got you.
-Come on!

813
00:58:37.347 --> 00:58:39.975
Watch your step. Watch. Don't look down.

814
00:58:46.064 --> 00:58:47.524
-Ah!
-Careful!

815
00:58:49.901 --> 00:58:53.238
Okay. Tighten up. everybody.
Make sure we're secure.

816
00:58:53.321 --> 00:58:55.073
No. I can't. I can't do this.

817
00:58:56.450 --> 00:58:58.827
I can't... I can't do this!
There's gotta be another way!

818
00:58:58.910 --> 00:59:00.912
Nathan! Just put one foot
in front of the other.

819
00:59:00.996 --> 00:59:02.914
Just follow me. I'll go first. okay?

820
00:59:03.665 --> 00:59:04.666
You've got this.

821
00:59:05.625 --> 00:59:07.169
All right. come on.

822
00:59:07.252 --> 00:59:08.712
-All right.
-You good?

823
00:59:08.795 --> 00:59:11.214
-Okay. You've got this.
-Be careful.

824
00:59:11.298 --> 00:59:13.008
Okay.

825
00:59:34.946 --> 00:59:37.282
Just keep going! Go!

826
00:59:39.701 --> 00:59:40.952
You good?

827
00:59:41.036 --> 00:59:42.746
Go. go. go!

828
00:59:56.093 --> 00:59:57.094
Hang on!

829
01:00:04.142 --> 01:00:06.478
-Everything okay?
-Yeah. Dad.

830
01:00:12.818 --> 01:00:14.694
Come on. Attaboy.

831
01:00:16.113 --> 01:00:17.114
Yeah.

832
01:00:17.739 --> 01:00:19.991
Okay. That's good.

833
01:00:22.285 --> 01:00:25.038
-Come on. you've got it! You've got it!
-Help me. Help me!

834
01:00:25.122 --> 01:00:26.248
Oh! Thank you.

835
01:00:27.499 --> 01:00:29.709
Right. almost there.
Just a little bit more.

836
01:00:29.793 --> 01:00:31.002
-You got it?
-Yeah.

837
01:00:31.086 --> 01:00:32.087
-You good?
-Yeah.

838
01:00:33.797 --> 01:00:34.798
That's it.

839
01:00:34.881 --> 01:00:36.716
Earthquake!

840
01:00:36.800 --> 01:00:38.593
Get down!

841
01:00:38.677 --> 01:00:41.429
-You've gotta be kidding me.
-We've gotta get off of here!

842
01:00:42.013 --> 01:00:43.014
Let's go.

843
01:00:43.807 --> 01:00:46.059
You go first. Allison.
I'll go behind Nathan.

844
01:00:46.143 --> 01:00:47.644
Just stay focused.

845
01:00:50.522 --> 01:00:52.357
That's it. You're okay!

846
01:00:57.362 --> 01:00:58.864
That's it. There you go.

847
01:01:02.325 --> 01:01:03.493
That's it. Nathan!

848
01:01:13.211 --> 01:01:15.630
-The line is breaking!
-Hang on!

849
01:01:21.011 --> 01:01:22.345
-Let's go!
-Get me off!

850
01:01:22.429 --> 01:01:24.598
Keep moving!

851
01:01:24.681 --> 01:01:27.350
Get me off of this! Get me off!

852
01:01:29.561 --> 01:01:32.147
Keep moving!

853
01:01:32.230 --> 01:01:33.857
-It won't hold!
-No. no. no. no. no!

854
01:01:33.940 --> 01:01:34.941
It won't hold!

855
01:01:35.025 --> 01:01:37.152
-Stay there! No!
-No! No!

856
01:01:37.235 --> 01:01:38.570
Nathan!

857
01:01:39.988 --> 01:01:41.781
-Nathan!
-Dad. Dad!

858
01:01:41.865 --> 01:01:44.451
Come on! Hold on!

859
01:01:44.534 --> 01:01:47.120
You've got it! It's okay.

860
01:01:47.204 --> 01:01:48.580
Please don't let me fall!

861
01:01:48.663 --> 01:01:51.041
-Hold on!
-Nathan! Nathan!

862
01:01:51.124 --> 01:01:52.542
Don't let me fall!

863
01:01:55.086 --> 01:01:56.171
Come on! That's it!

864
01:01:56.254 --> 01:01:58.173
It won't hold!

865
01:01:59.758 --> 01:02:01.301
-Nathan! Keep moving!
-Come on!

866
01:02:01.384 --> 01:02:03.970
Come on. you've gotta go. That's it.

867
01:02:04.554 --> 01:02:06.181
Come on. kiddo! Almost there.

868
01:02:07.474 --> 01:02:08.475
Come on. Nathan!

869
01:02:08.558 --> 01:02:09.893
Hurry!

870
01:02:11.144 --> 01:02:12.479
Take my hand!

871
01:02:13.063 --> 01:02:14.064
Don't look down!

872
01:02:15.941 --> 01:02:19.236
Come on! Okay. let's go!
Let's go. Let's go. Nathan.

873
01:02:19.319 --> 01:02:21.029
Come on! That's it.

874
01:02:22.322 --> 01:02:23.323
Come on!

875
01:02:28.954 --> 01:02:30.121
Oh. my God!

876
01:03:09.828 --> 01:03:11.079
What the hell?

877
01:03:25.385 --> 01:03:27.262
-Is that it?
-No. That's not it.

878
01:03:27.345 --> 01:03:28.555
It's much further south.

879
01:03:29.347 --> 01:03:30.682
It's totally dead.

880
01:03:31.433 --> 01:03:33.310
What if the Clarke crater's like this?

881
01:03:33.393 --> 01:03:35.770
This could've been a fragment
that hit a week ago.

882
01:03:35.854 --> 01:03:37.022
Or five years ago.

883
01:03:37.897 --> 01:03:39.107
Hey...

884
01:03:40.900 --> 01:03:43.028
This is what we're doing.
We're gonna keep going.

885
01:03:45.780 --> 01:03:47.157
-Yeah.
-Okay.

886
01:03:54.706 --> 01:03:56.875
Uh... English?

887
01:03:57.834 --> 01:03:59.044
Who are you?

888
01:03:59.753 --> 01:04:02.005
My name is. uh. John Garrity.

889
01:04:03.006 --> 01:04:05.383
This is my wife. Allison. My son. Nathan.

890
01:04:06.551 --> 01:04:07.969
What are you doing here?

891
01:04:08.053 --> 01:04:10.055
We're trying to get to the Clarke Crater.

892
01:04:23.443 --> 01:04:24.486
I am Denis Laurent.

893
01:04:25.153 --> 01:04:26.154
Hi.

894
01:04:27.781 --> 01:04:28.865
You look hungry.

895
01:04:30.784 --> 01:04:32.035
We don't have anything to trade.

896
01:04:33.370 --> 01:04:34.496
Ah. but you do.

897
01:04:35.413 --> 01:04:36.623
It's called company.

898
01:04:45.131 --> 01:04:47.342
So. do you always shoot at people?

899
01:04:47.425 --> 01:04:49.302
It's a dangerous area.

900
01:04:49.386 --> 01:04:50.804
You're lucky I found you.

901
01:04:50.887 --> 01:04:52.597
Most people aren't so nice.

902
01:05:15.453 --> 01:05:16.538
This is us.

903
01:05:17.580 --> 01:05:18.957
What was this place?

904
01:05:19.958 --> 01:05:22.836
This is our mail sorting center.

905
01:05:23.420 --> 01:05:25.672
Nobody tries to take this from you?

906
01:05:26.923 --> 01:05:28.049
They've tried.

907
01:05:30.468 --> 01:05:32.720
This is your
power supply. You built this?

908
01:05:32.804 --> 01:05:35.306
Yes. We draw power from the solar panels

909
01:05:35.390 --> 01:05:37.976
into the car's power bank.
and we have electricity.

910
01:05:38.476 --> 01:05:40.311
It powers our air purifiers.

911
01:05:40.395 --> 01:05:42.939
It's not perfect.
but it's the best we can do.

912
01:05:52.740 --> 01:05:55.702
John. Allison. Nathan...

913
01:05:57.370 --> 01:05:59.038
And my daughter. Camille.

914
01:06:00.415 --> 01:06:01.624
Nice to meet you.

915
01:06:02.375 --> 01:06:03.835
She does not speak.

916
01:06:03.918 --> 01:06:04.919
Her nervous system.

917
01:06:05.003 --> 01:06:06.880
The radiation has taken its toll.

918
01:06:09.591 --> 01:06:11.593
Very good.

919
01:06:11.676 --> 01:06:13.136
-Yeah. c'est bon.
-It's good. yeah.

920
01:06:13.219 --> 01:06:14.971
Closest thing you get to
a French restaurant today.

921
01:06:15.054 --> 01:06:16.598
Thank you so much.

922
01:06:16.681 --> 01:06:17.765
-It's great.
-Very good.

923
01:06:17.849 --> 01:06:19.851
It's very nice to have a home-cooked meal.

924
01:06:19.934 --> 01:06:22.645
So. you are trying to reach the crater?

925
01:06:23.271 --> 01:06:24.814
-Yeah.
-Yeah. we are.

926
01:06:24.898 --> 01:06:27.901
They say the crater is La Terre Promise...

927
01:06:27.984 --> 01:06:30.195
how you say... The Promised Land.

928
01:06:31.029 --> 01:06:32.489
Humanity's last chance.

929
01:06:34.365 --> 01:06:35.533
It could be so.

930
01:06:35.617 --> 01:06:36.910
We've also heard that...

931
01:06:37.911 --> 01:06:39.496
maybe people have gone there.

932
01:06:40.497 --> 01:06:42.040
That region is too dangerous...

933
01:06:42.540 --> 01:06:43.875
The Western Alliance.

934
01:06:43.958 --> 01:06:46.127
including remnants of the French Army.

935
01:06:46.628 --> 01:06:48.171
are defending it from an invasion

936
01:06:48.254 --> 01:06:49.923
by the Eastern Coalition.

937
01:06:50.006 --> 01:06:52.217
who want to take the crater
for its resources.

938
01:06:52.717 --> 01:06:54.844
There is heavy fighting
on the entire front.

939
01:06:56.471 --> 01:06:57.805
From Lyon to Berne.

940
01:06:58.765 --> 01:07:00.266
Only two cities left standing.

941
01:07:01.559 --> 01:07:03.394
It is impossible to get through.

942
01:07:07.440 --> 01:07:09.234
Where'd you get all these things?

943
01:07:09.817 --> 01:07:11.319
My dad sometimes will go outside

944
01:07:11.402 --> 01:07:14.656
and try to find stuff that
was not completely destroyed.

945
01:07:15.657 --> 01:07:17.158
So we could make a home.

946
01:07:19.661 --> 01:07:21.788
-Can I show you something?
-Sure.

947
01:07:22.372 --> 01:07:24.958
I made this in the bunker. in Greenland.

948
01:07:25.041 --> 01:07:27.877
It's. um. it's the sky we can never see.

949
01:07:29.003 --> 01:07:32.090
It's what we would have seen
if we... we could've seen.

950
01:07:32.590 --> 01:07:33.841
You hold that end.

951
01:07:35.093 --> 01:07:37.971
-Which one”? Oh...
-Oh. sorry. Okay.

952
01:07:41.599 --> 01:07:43.893
-You come down as well. yeah.
-Oh. okay.

953
01:07:48.439 --> 01:07:50.358
So. these are the star signs.

954
01:07:50.441 --> 01:07:52.193
Do you know what star sign you are?

955
01:07:52.986 --> 01:07:54.404
I think I'm Aquarius.

956
01:07:54.904 --> 01:07:56.072
Oh. that's air.

957
01:07:56.739 --> 01:07:58.616
-I'm a Pisces.
-Mmm...

958
01:07:58.700 --> 01:08:00.451
So I'm a fish.

959
01:08:01.536 --> 01:08:03.496
I read somewhere that...

960
01:08:03.580 --> 01:08:05.582
that Pisces and Aquariuses get along well.

961
01:08:32.233 --> 01:08:34.527
Oh... hey.

962
01:08:34.611 --> 01:08:35.612
Hi.

963
01:08:35.695 --> 01:08:37.322
How long have you been up for?

964
01:08:39.073 --> 01:08:41.200
-Most of the night.
-Oh...

965
01:08:42.243 --> 01:08:43.369
Oh.

966
01:08:45.955 --> 01:08:47.874
Hey. the night before our wedding...

967
01:08:49.208 --> 01:08:51.252
My dad took you aside
into this little side room

968
01:08:51.336 --> 01:08:52.337
or whatever it was.

969
01:08:54.422 --> 01:08:55.798
He told me he loved me.

970
01:08:56.591 --> 01:08:57.967
Like a son.

971
01:09:00.136 --> 01:09:01.679
What did he really say to you?

972
01:09:07.018 --> 01:09:08.811
Oh. he made me promise something.

973
01:09:13.524 --> 01:09:15.318
That I would take care of you...

974
01:09:16.694 --> 01:09:18.237
until my last breath.

975
01:09:25.036 --> 01:09:26.412
Oh. hey...

976
01:10:02.990 --> 01:10:06.452
This one... is more up to date than yours.

977
01:10:06.536 --> 01:10:09.580
The Western Alliance defends the crater

978
01:10:09.664 --> 01:10:11.874
so people can live there
as a free society.

979
01:10:11.958 --> 01:10:13.209
As I said last night.

980
01:10:13.292 --> 01:10:15.628
this entire region is a heavy war zone.

981
01:10:16.129 --> 01:10:17.964
but there is a way around.

982
01:10:18.589 --> 01:10:21.592
I recommend you take this way.

983
01:10:21.676 --> 01:10:22.760
Clermont-Ferrand.

984
01:10:23.594 --> 01:10:24.971
Then down to Valence.

985
01:10:25.847 --> 01:10:26.848
Less fighting.

986
01:10:26.931 --> 01:10:30.518
The crater is protected
by several mountain ranges.

987
01:10:30.601 --> 01:10:32.854
Through the first. there is only one way.

988
01:10:33.438 --> 01:10:34.522
The pass.

989
01:10:36.190 --> 01:10:38.818
It will be very difficult
to move through this area.

990
01:10:39.569 --> 01:10:41.946
The pass is protected by
my friend's battalion.

991
01:10:42.029 --> 01:10:43.322
of the Western Alliance.

992
01:10:43.990 --> 01:10:45.324
So when you get there.

993
01:10:45.408 --> 01:10:47.493
you will ask for Commander Jeunet.

994
01:10:47.577 --> 01:10:50.955
-Jeunet.
-And you will give him this.

995
01:10:52.874 --> 01:10:54.375
He'll know I sent you.

996
01:10:55.501 --> 01:10:56.711
He can get you through.

997
01:11:01.215 --> 01:11:02.258
Thank you.

998
01:11:08.264 --> 01:11:10.391
There is. uh. one more thing.

999
01:11:13.978 --> 01:11:15.062
Oh. look...

1000
01:11:15.897 --> 01:11:18.608
I don't know what
awaits you at the crater.

1001
01:11:20.568 --> 01:11:23.613
But I am convinced this is where
the world will be reborn.

1002
01:11:28.618 --> 01:11:29.744
Take Camille with you.

1003
01:11:32.705 --> 01:11:33.831
Please.

1004
01:11:38.336 --> 01:11:39.420
Take our daughter.

1005
01:11:42.590 --> 01:11:44.342
I couldn't do it myself.

1006
01:11:44.425 --> 01:11:47.094
My wife. she can't travel.

1007
01:11:47.178 --> 01:11:48.221
You see that.

1008
01:11:49.138 --> 01:11:51.766
I have yet to meet anyone else
I would trust with this.

1009
01:11:52.934 --> 01:11:55.394
I beg of you. John...

1010
01:11:56.395 --> 01:11:58.022
- I beg of you.

1011
01:11:58.606 --> 01:12:00.483
-Um...
-We'll take her.

1012
01:12:03.778 --> 01:12:04.904
We'll get her there.

1013
01:12:09.492 --> 01:12:10.535
We'll get her there.

1014
01:12:14.038 --> 01:12:15.706
We'll get her there.

1015
01:13:51.427 --> 01:13:53.012
It should be a straight shot from here.

1016
01:13:54.555 --> 01:13:56.682
The pass is just before
the outside of the crater.

1017
01:14:03.272 --> 01:14:04.607
You guys okay?

1018
01:14:13.240 --> 01:14:15.743
Maybe we should stop. Take a break.

1019
01:14:17.370 --> 01:14:18.788
Yeah.

1020
01:14:35.513 --> 01:14:39.058
Would you rather read minds
or be invisible?

1021
01:14:45.940 --> 01:14:47.149
Read minds.

1022
01:14:48.025 --> 01:14:49.026
Be invisible.

1023
01:14:55.449 --> 01:14:56.909
Read minds.

1024
01:14:56.993 --> 01:14:58.452
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

1025
01:14:59.120 --> 01:15:02.873
Uh. would you rather
have really small hands.

1026
01:15:02.957 --> 01:15:04.291
or really big feet?

1027
01:15:04.375 --> 01:15:05.376
Big feet.

1028
01:15:05.459 --> 01:15:06.752
How do you walk with big feet?

1029
01:15:06.836 --> 01:15:08.212
-Yeah. Small hands.
-How does that work?

1030
01:15:08.295 --> 01:15:09.380
You already have small hands.

1031
01:15:09.463 --> 01:15:10.840
-I do not.
-Show me.

1032
01:15:11.966 --> 01:15:13.551
I have normal hands. Look at yours.

1033
01:15:13.634 --> 01:15:14.635
-They're huge!
-No.

1034
01:15:14.719 --> 01:15:17.096
See? Look. Normal. See?

1035
01:15:17.179 --> 01:15:20.391
Would you rather fight
50 chicken-sized horses

1036
01:15:20.474 --> 01:15:22.476
or one horse-sized chicken?

1037
01:15:22.560 --> 01:15:23.853
What?

1038
01:15:23.936 --> 01:15:25.604
Fifty horse-sized chickens?

1039
01:15:25.688 --> 01:15:27.523
-50 horse-sized chickens?
-That's...

1040
01:15:27.606 --> 01:15:29.692
-Fifty...
-Chicken-sized horses.

1041
01:15:29.775 --> 01:15:30.776
-Fifty...
-What?

1042
01:15:30.860 --> 01:15:32.445
-You said chicken-sized...
-Okay!

1043
01:16:27.625 --> 01:16:28.793
To the crater?

1044
01:16:28.876 --> 01:16:31.712
You know you're gonna have to go
through a war zone to get there?

1045
01:16:32.296 --> 01:16:33.547
You'll never make it.

1046
01:16:34.465 --> 01:16:35.800
Maybe you can help us.

1047
01:17:02.618 --> 01:17:04.620
This pass is
the only way through.

1048
01:17:04.703 --> 01:17:06.372
Commander Jeunet is stationed ahead.

1049
01:17:16.257 --> 01:17:18.926
Okay. follow me close.
Move as I move. okay?

1050
01:17:19.009 --> 01:17:20.511
-Okay.
-Come on.

1051
01:17:23.722 --> 01:17:24.807
Quickly! Quickly!

1052
01:17:27.726 --> 01:17:29.520
Down. down!

1053
01:17:34.024 --> 01:17:35.776
Let's go. let's go. let's go!

1054
01:17:35.860 --> 01:17:36.944
Come on. Nathan!

1055
01:17:37.862 --> 01:17:40.614
Follow me! Follow me! Run!

1056
01:17:40.698 --> 01:17:41.866
Run fast!

1057
01:17:43.325 --> 01:17:44.660
Keep moving!

1058
01:17:45.911 --> 01:17:48.205
Stay low! Keep your head down!

1059
01:17:49.582 --> 01:17:50.833
Stop. Stop. stop. stop!

1060
01:17:50.916 --> 01:17:52.418
-Oh. my God.
-Get down!

1061
01:17:54.336 --> 01:17:56.172
Let's go. let's go. let's go!

1062
01:17:59.300 --> 01:18:00.926
Come on! Come on! Come on!

1063
01:18:13.230 --> 01:18:16.150
Come on! Come on! Let's go!

1064
01:18:16.233 --> 01:18:18.944
Up to the bunker! Up to the bunker!

1065
01:18:23.407 --> 01:18:25.618
All right. go!
Go. go. go. go!

1066
01:18:28.662 --> 01:18:29.830
Nathan. head down!

1067
01:18:32.625 --> 01:18:33.751
Stay low!

1068
01:18:36.670 --> 01:18:38.631
-Jump. Nathan!
-Get down into the trench!

1069
01:18:45.054 --> 01:18:47.640
-John. you okay?
-Yeah. I'm okay.

1070
01:18:48.599 --> 01:18:49.808
-Okay. Come on. Let's go.
-Okay.

1071
01:18:49.892 --> 01:18:51.060
-Come on!
-Uh!

1072
01:18:59.610 --> 01:19:01.570
Go. go. go. go. go!

1073
01:19:10.663 --> 01:19:11.664
This way.

1074
01:19:13.874 --> 01:19:15.584
Up the ladder! Up the ladder!

1075
01:19:16.919 --> 01:19:19.213
-Let's go. let's go!
-Nathan. go. go. go!

1076
01:19:19.296 --> 01:19:20.756
All right. All right! Get up! Get up!

1077
01:19:20.839 --> 01:19:21.840
-Hey...

1078
01:19:21.924 --> 01:19:23.467
Keep walking through the forest

1079
01:19:23.550 --> 01:19:25.010
in that direction. all right?

1080
01:19:25.094 --> 01:19:27.221
Jeunet is the commander of that area.

1081
01:19:27.304 --> 01:19:28.305
-All right?
-Okay.

1082
01:19:28.389 --> 01:19:29.473
I need to get back to my unit.

1083
01:19:29.556 --> 01:19:30.849
-Merci!
-Okay.

1084
01:19:30.933 --> 01:19:32.226
-Good luck!
-Thank you!

1085
01:19:32.309 --> 01:19:33.894
-Let's go.
-Thank you!

1086
01:19:33.978 --> 01:19:35.104
Boone chance.

1087
01:20:07.803 --> 01:20:09.054
That must be their camp.

1088
01:20:11.807 --> 01:20:13.058
Those mountains.

1089
01:20:14.143 --> 01:20:15.436
They were never there before.

1090
01:20:22.026 --> 01:20:23.694
We're getting close to the crater.

1091
01:20:55.559 --> 01:20:56.643
He's there.

1092
01:21:04.193 --> 01:21:05.736
Do you speak English?

1093
01:21:05.819 --> 01:21:07.738
-Oui.
-We're looking for.

1094
01:21:07.821 --> 01:21:10.074
uh. Commander Jeunet?

1095
01:21:11.033 --> 01:21:14.078
Her father. Denis Laurent.

1096
01:21:14.161 --> 01:21:16.580
is old friends with Commander Jeunet.

1097
01:21:16.663 --> 01:21:20.417
and he said that Commander Jeunet
would take us to the crater.

1098
01:21:24.838 --> 01:21:25.839
Come.

1099
01:21:26.882 --> 01:21:27.925
Commander Jeunet.

1100
01:21:34.640 --> 01:21:37.309
People wait days for that bus. I'm sorry.

1101
01:21:39.061 --> 01:21:40.396
There is nothing I can do for you.

1102
01:21:41.313 --> 01:21:42.648
Now. please leave my tent.

1103
01:21:45.275 --> 01:21:47.569
Is there somebody else we can speak to

1104
01:21:47.653 --> 01:21:49.321
or we can talk to?

1105
01:21:49.405 --> 01:21:50.447
Get them out of here.

1106
01:21:51.365 --> 01:21:53.867
No. hey. No. hold on. Hold on. Wait.

1107
01:21:54.868 --> 01:21:56.412
Please. let me. Plea...

1108
01:21:57.955 --> 01:22:00.082
Look. we've been through a lot.

1109
01:22:02.084 --> 01:22:03.377
We're not gonna hurt anybody.

1110
01:22:03.460 --> 01:22:05.587
All we wanna do is get
to the crater. That's all.

1111
01:22:09.758 --> 01:22:10.759
I'm dying.

1112
01:22:11.718 --> 01:22:13.971
I don't know how much longer and I...

1113
01:22:14.054 --> 01:22:17.141
I promised my family
that I'll get them to safety.

1114
01:22:17.766 --> 01:22:19.476
Please don't take this away from us.

1115
01:22:24.773 --> 01:22:25.941
Please.

1116
01:22:36.326 --> 01:22:38.287
There's a
transport bus just past there.

1117
01:22:38.954 --> 01:22:40.956
It's bringing people to the crater.

1118
01:22:41.039 --> 01:22:42.749
Luc will take you. Go now.

1119
01:22:43.750 --> 01:22:44.835
Thank you.

1120
01:22:46.044 --> 01:22:47.045
Boone chance.

1121
01:23:45.312 --> 01:23:46.396
Insurgents!

1122
01:23:47.105 --> 01:23:48.732
All of you. stay on the bus!

1123
01:23:57.074 --> 01:23:58.951
-Oh! John!
-Start the bus!

1124
01:24:08.794 --> 01:24:11.004
This is our bus now!

1125
01:24:11.088 --> 01:24:12.714
Let's go! Everybody off the bus!

1126
01:24:13.799 --> 01:24:15.133
Line up against the bus!

1127
01:24:15.759 --> 01:24:17.302
Move! Move!

1128
01:24:19.221 --> 01:24:20.389
Line up against the bus!

1129
01:24:21.557 --> 01:24:23.433
I promised you I was gonna
get you to the crater.

1130
01:24:24.726 --> 01:24:25.769
Let's go!

1131
01:24:26.728 --> 01:24:28.188
-Go. go.
-Move!

1132
01:24:28.272 --> 01:24:31.567
-Follow me.
-Go. son. Go. It's all right.

1133
01:24:31.650 --> 01:24:32.985
-It'll be okay.
-Move!

1134
01:24:36.238 --> 01:24:37.364
You. let's go!

1135
01:24:38.240 --> 01:24:39.908
Get off the bus!

1136
01:24:41.410 --> 01:24:42.661
Move! Move!

1137
01:24:43.829 --> 01:24:46.915
Let's go! Move! Off the bus!

1138
01:24:53.171 --> 01:24:54.548
No!

1139
01:25:02.639 --> 01:25:03.932
Oh. my God!

1140
01:25:21.575 --> 01:25:22.951
-Dad?
-Oh. my God!

1141
01:25:23.035 --> 01:25:24.494
Dad!

1142
01:25:27.080 --> 01:25:28.874
Dad. Dad!

1143
01:25:31.293 --> 01:25:32.294
I'm okay.

1144
01:25:33.003 --> 01:25:34.504
We've gotta get you help!

1145
01:25:34.588 --> 01:25:35.714
Oh. my God!

1146
01:25:36.923 --> 01:25:40.135
All right. we've gotta go.
There might be more of them.

1147
01:25:40.218 --> 01:25:41.261
I'll drive!

1148
01:25:41.345 --> 01:25:44.139
-Get up! Get up! Let's go!
-Okay.

1149
01:25:54.650 --> 01:25:56.485
It's okay.

1150
01:25:58.070 --> 01:25:59.821
-It's okay.
-Nathan. keep pressure on it!

1151
01:26:01.365 --> 01:26:03.283
Push hard. Yeah.

1152
01:26:10.499 --> 01:26:11.667
It's okay. mate.

1153
01:26:12.376 --> 01:26:13.627
Ah. that's it.

1154
01:26:46.451 --> 01:26:47.452
That's it.

1155
01:26:54.209 --> 01:26:56.086
We're stuck. Can you walk a little bit?

1156
01:26:56.169 --> 01:26:57.212
-Yeah.
-Hold onto that.

1157
01:28:01.443 --> 01:28:03.570
Oh. my God. it's real.

1158
01:28:07.449 --> 01:28:08.825
Oh. it's so beautiful.

1159
01:28:08.909 --> 01:28:10.494
Oh. yeah.

1160
01:28:10.577 --> 01:28:13.663
Hold on. Let me
take this in for a second.

1161
01:28:15.999 --> 01:28:18.126
Almost there. It's just a little further.

1162
01:28:18.919 --> 01:28:20.045
We'll get you fixed up.

1163
01:28:33.600 --> 01:28:34.810
You're gonna be okay.

1164
01:28:35.644 --> 01:28:36.645
Yeah?

1165
01:28:41.650 --> 01:28:42.859
You did great. Dad.

1166
01:28:44.361 --> 01:28:45.362
We made it!

1167
01:28:46.404 --> 01:28:47.572
-We did it!
-Yeah.

1168
01:28:49.032 --> 01:28:50.534
Yeah. we did it.

1169
01:28:57.749 --> 01:28:58.750
What a view.

1170
01:29:00.252 --> 01:29:02.337
Think of the world you could build here.

1171
01:29:09.052 --> 01:29:10.053
-John!
-Oh. yeah...

1172
01:29:12.973 --> 01:29:13.974
John...

1173
01:29:15.267 --> 01:29:16.268
John?

1174
01:29:33.368 --> 01:29:34.703
Thank you.

1175
01:29:37.289 --> 01:29:38.707
For being my girl.

1176
01:30:09.321 --> 01:30:10.322
May the...

1177
01:30:11.489 --> 01:30:14.159
May the roads rise up to meet you.

1178
01:30:17.746 --> 01:30:20.332
May the... May the wind
always be at your back.

1179
01:30:24.336 --> 01:30:29.299
May the... May the sun shine warm
upon your face.

1180
01:30:31.426 --> 01:30:34.679
And the rain fall.
fall softly upon your fields.

1181
01:30:38.642 --> 01:30:39.935
Travel safe. Dad.

1182
01:31:17.305 --> 01:31:19.432
You have a chance
to start over again.

1183
01:31:23.979 --> 01:31:26.398
The chance to build a better place.

1184
01:31:28.733 --> 01:31:29.985
A better world.

1185
01:31:32.612 --> 01:31:35.198
One led by kindness and compassion

1186
01:31:35.281 --> 01:31:37.242
and understanding.

1187
01:31:43.456 --> 01:31:44.874
One not just worth living in...

1188
01:31:46.960 --> 01:31:48.086
but living for.

1189
01:31:53.174 --> 01:31:55.093
And though I won't see the sunrise...

1190
01:31:57.095 --> 01:31:58.096
you will.

1191
01:31:59.014 --> 01:32:00.932
And you'll carry that light with you...

1192
01:32:03.018 --> 01:32:04.644
because that's what we're built for.

1193
01:32:29.169 --> 01:32:30.628
Tomorrow belongs to you.

1194
01:32:32.756 --> 01:32:33.757
To all of you.

1195
01:32:34.924 --> 01:32:36.009
Safe journey on.

